reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: This was the perfect fit for my bar height counters to create a neat little bar space to store all my liquor and a little wine too. I have custom wine glasses that have a larger than normal base and the still fit into the glass rack beautifully. This was easy to assemble and very sturdy too. There is a slight misalignment of the doors but it is only aesthetic and does not affect the functionality at all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble and looks nice
reviews.reviewText: This is an easy to assemble little bar cart, good quality for the price. Doors were very easy to assemble unlike some other pieces I’ve recently put together. You need a screwdriver to assemble which is not in the instructions but it does come with the required Allen wrenches.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks like a high-end piece of furniture when assembled
reviews.reviewText: As with most furniture these days, this item has to be assembled from absolute scratch, but the instructions are easy to follow and the parts are well-marked. Took me about an hour. With the LED light strips, and the color of the wood veneer (I ordered the dark brown), once it's assembled, this piece looks fantastic. You could hardly tell it wasn't purchased in a high-end furniture store. It's so roomy, too. It holds all of my various and sundry wine glasses AND alcohol in the underneath cabinet and it's fun to display your pretty unopened wine bottles in the top wine storage. Then, how cool is it to have a multi-color LED light with remote to play with, too?! I really like this piece. One of my favorite Amazon purchases from this past year.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Safe, secure, and keeps the cat out!
reviews.reviewText: This is exactly what I needed to keep my cat off of my liquor bottles. It fit allllllmost perfectly under my counter, so with the top off it fits just right.The magnetic door releases are good, a little weird to get used to but not the worst in the world. Assembly took about 45ish minutes, which isn’t that bad! Instructions mostly make sense and the pieces are mostly clear as to where they go.My cat kept climbing on my liquor bottles, so I purchased this to keep him off of the expensive stuff ;)Would buy again!
